###########################################################################################################

DESCRIPTION : TO FIND OUT HOW MANY MO CREATE / DELETE REQUESTS CAN BE SUPPORTED MY MULTIPLE NODES IN ONE VM.

###########################################################################################################

PRE-USECASE SETUP:-
   
   -> THE CREATE MO REQUEST NETCONF COMMAND SHOULD BE GENERATED FIRST WHICH IS DEPENDENT ON USE CASE OF HOW MANY MO CREATE REQUEST/DELETE REQUEST SHOULD BE DONE
   
   -> TO GENERATE THE COMMAND WITH 'N' CREATE/DELETE MO'S , gen_req.sh SHOULD BE TRIGGERED WITH NUMBER OF MO CREATE AS INPUT PARAMETER AND THE NODES FILE WITH NODE NAME AND SIMULATION SHOULD BE PRESENT IN THE CURRENT WORKING DIRECTORY.
        Ex:- sh gen_req.sh 100 nodes.txt will create a command with 100 mo create requests with output command in <NODENAME>.txt 
   
   -> SIMILARLY FOR DELETE REQ sh gen_req_delete.sh <number of delete request> SHOULD BE TRIGGERED.

############################################################################################################

USE-CASE SETUP:-

    -> BSC NODES SHOULD BE KEPT IN A INPUT FILE WITH NODE_NAME,NODE_IP.

    -> NETCONF SUBSCRIPTION SHOULD BE CREATED BEFORE THE USE CASE BY TRIGGERING subscriber.sh <node_file> <time_out> <logging true or false>
        -> FOR GENERATING NODE FILE , getNodes.sh SHOULD BE RUN IN THE BOX WHERE THE NODES ARE PRESENT WHICH WILL GENERATE AllNodes.job.

    -> PRMN REQUEST AND RESPONSE SHOULD BE GENERATED IN THE BOX WHERE THE NODES ARE PRESENT SO THAT THE PREVIOUS ACTIVITIES ON THE NODES ARE NEGLECTED.

    -> NOW THE MAIN SCRIPT trigger.sh <num of nodes> SHOULD BE TRIGGERED.
        -> num of nodes SHOULD BE PRESENT IN NODE FILE WITH NODE NAME AND NODE IP.

############################################################################################################

AFTER USE-CASE :-

    -> generatereqprmn.sh and generateresprmn.sh SHOULD BE TRIGGERED IN THE BOX WHERE NODES ARE PRESENT.

    -> calci_time.sh SHOULD BE TRIGGERED WITH INPUTS AS <PRMNRESPONSE.log> <PRMNREQUESTS.log> <RESULTS.txt> <nodes.txt> <NUMBER_OF_MO_CREATED>

    -> RESULTS ARE STORED IN observations.txt

    
